<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When uploading an existing file from a directory that contains space in it's name, the uploaded file's name is actually the part of the directory before the space instead of the expected file's name.</p>

<p>Reporduction code:
(create a file named /tmp/With Space/wow.txt):</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$client = new Zend_Http_Client('<a href="http://localhost/Framework/tests/testUploads.php">http://localhost/Framework/tests/testUploads.php</a>');
$client-&gt;setFileUpload('/tmp/With Space/wow.txt', 'somefile');

$res = $client-&gt;request('POST');
echo $res-&gt;getBody() . "\n";
</code></pre>

